# UX Requirements for Beauty by Raquel Nicole

## User Personas
1. **Beauty Enthusiast (Primary):** Female, 22-35, seeks regular lash/brow maintenance
2. **Busy Professional:** Female, 30-45, values efficiency and recurring appointments
3. **First-Time Visitor:** Female, 18-25, trying services for the first time
4. **Returning Loyalist:** Female, 25-40, existing client seeking loyalty perks

## User Journey Optimization
- **Awareness:** Google search, Instagram discovery, word-of-mouth
- **Research:** Service pages, pricing, before/after galleries, reviews
- **Booking:** One-click appointment scheduling with clear CTAs
- **Service Experience:** Quality service with follow-up marketing
- **Retention:** Membership programs, automated reminders, referral rewards

## Key UX Pain Points to Address
- **Slow Page Speed:** Target < 1 second load time
- **Poor Navigation:** Clear service organization and booking flow
- **No Trust Signals:** Testimonials, reviews, before/after galleries
- **Booking Friction:** Streamlined booking with automated reminders
- **Mobile Optimization:** Responsive design with touch-friendly elements

## Conversion Optimization
- **Hero Section:** Immediate "Book Now" CTA with service highlights
- **Service Cards:** Clear pricing, descriptions, and booking buttons
- **Trust Building:** Testimonials slider, client gallery, review integration
- **Membership Promotion:** Highlight loyalty programs and referral rewards
- **Mobile Booking:** Optimized for quick mobile appointment scheduling

## Accessibility Standards
- **WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance:** Proper contrast ratios and focus states
- **Keyboard Navigation:** Full keyboard accessibility
- **Screen Reader Support:** Semantic HTML and ARIA labels
- **Touch Targets:** Minimum 44px for mobile interactions
- **Loading States:** Clear feedback for all user actions

## Content Strategy
- **Service Pages:** Detailed descriptions, pricing, FAQs, before/after photos
- **Blog Content:** Educational posts on lash care, brow styling, beauty trends
- **Local SEO:** Location-specific content and Google Business Profile integration
- **Social Proof:** Client testimonials, reviews, transformation galleries

## Performance Requirements
- **Core Web Vitals:** LCP < 1s, TBT < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- **Mobile-First:** Optimized layouts for mobile booking
- **Image Optimization:** WebP format, lazy loading, proper sizing
- **Caching:** CDN implementation for faster asset delivery

## Booking Experience
- **Square Integration:** Real-time availability and secure payments
- **Automated Reminders:** Email/SMS confirmations and follow-ups
- **Membership Management:** Loyalty program dashboard for returning clients
- **Referral System:** Automated rewards for new client acquisition
